As part of its companies Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR), organisers of the maiden edition of the Tush My Apartment Reality TV Show has announced that the registration and housemates selection have began. Speaking during a media parley, the chairman of Tush My Home Global Limited, Dr. Fred Ayodeji Mafikuyomi, disclosed that the show is for Nigerians from the age of 18 who want to be famous and want their lives changed as it dwells more on improving the living condition of an average Nigerian with the sole aim of putting smiles on their respective faces. The show however targets all Nigerians, three Contestants who make it to the final will get their apartment renovated or rent a new apartment to the tune of N1.5Million Naira, N1Million Naira and Five Hundred Thousand Naira respectively and also the show will be organized every quarter. Dr Mafikuyomi explained the processes of the show saying, ‘ In order to boost the living conditions, restore the pride of average Nigerians and to put a smile on their faces, Tush My Apartment Reality Show is introduced to enhance the lifestyle of Nigerians by using a team of professionally trained and highly resourceful experts to execute a free and complete makeover of an existing apartment owned by 3 lucky Nigerians and Contestants in the Show or rent an apartment for the winners if necessary.’ Mafikuyomi also encouraged Nigerians and brands to support the show, which according to him, respects our religion, culture, morale, social, norms and ethics.